  "text": "The Rust compiler uses a multi-layered architecture for trait method resolution and error reporting. **Candidate Collection** happens at two main levels:\n\n1. **Trait Candidate Assembly** (compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/traits/select/candidate_assembly.rs): The `assemble_candidates` function is the primary entry point that examines in-scope trait implementations and assembles a list of candidates for trait obligation resolution.\n\n2. **Method Candidate Probing** (compiler/rustc_hir_typeck/src/method/probe.rs): When resolving method calls on a receiver type, the probe module uses `probe_for_name` and `probe_for_name_many` to gather method candidates from inherent implementations and trait extensions. The `pick_all_method` function iterates through autoderef steps to find applicable methods, and `consider_candidates` filters these candidates and returns either a unique pick or an ambiguity error. When multiple candidates are equally valid, `consider_candidates` (line 1727-1741) creates `MethodError::Ambiguity` by collecting the candidate sources.\n\n3. **Associated Item Candidate Collection** (compiler/rustc_hir_analysis/src/hir_ty_lowering/mod.rs): The `probe_single_bound_for_assoc_item` function searches for associated items (types, methods, constants) within trait bounds and reports ambiguity when multiple matching bounds define the same item (E0221).\n\n**Ambiguous Method Error Reporting** uses three integrated systems:\n\n1. **Associated Item Ambiguity** (compiler/rustc_hir_analysis/src/hir_ty_lowering/mod.rs, lines 1121-1200): When `probe_single_bound_for_assoc_item` finds multiple matching candidates, it directly reports an `AmbiguousAssocItem` error (from compiler/rustc_hir_analysis/src/errors.rs) with error code E0221 for types and E0222 for equality bindings.\n\n2. **Trait Selection Ambiguity** (compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/error_reporting/traits/ambiguity.rs): The `maybe_report_ambiguity` function handles ambiguity in trait obligation resolution, while `compute_applicable_impls_for_diagnostics` computes which trait implementations could satisfy an ambiguous obligation for error reporting purposes.\n\n3. **Method Ambiguity Suggestions** (compiler/rustc_hir_typeck/src/method/suggest.rs, line 221-223): When `MethodError::Ambiguity` is encountered, the error reporting module provides structured suggestions by examining the ambiguous candidate sources.\n\nThe ICE during trait method resolution likely occurs when an assumption about candidate uniqueness is violated, or when candidate collection doesn't properly handle certain trait hierarchy edge cases."
}

